# Flutter / Quze PWA Rules

## Layout and Responsiveness

- Use `ResponsiveBreakpoints` from `lib/widgets/responsive_layout.dart` for breakpoints
- Phone: < 600px | Tablet: 600-1024px | Desktop: >= 1024px
- Use `kMinTouchTargetSize` (44.0) for buttons, list tiles, checkboxes

```dart
// Use ResponsiveBreakpoints for layout
if (ResponsiveBreakpoints.isPhone(context)) { ... }
final isSmallScreen = MediaQuery.sizeOf(context).width < 600;

// Min touch target for interactive elements
SizedBox(height: kMinTouchTargetSize, child: ElevatedButton(...));
```

## API and Config

- API base URL: use `ApiConfigService.getApiBaseUrl()` / `ApiConfigService.setApiBaseUrl()`
- All HTTP calls go through `DatabaseService` in `login_page.dart`; use `DatabaseService.baseUrl`
- WebSocket URL: `DatabaseService.getWebSocketUrl(userId)`

## Structure

- Pages in `lib/pages/`, admin pages in `lib/pages/admin/`
- Services in `lib/services/` (e.g. `UserDataService`, `ApiConfigService`)
- Shared widgets in `lib/widgets/`

## PWA

- Brand: Quze in `web/manifest.json`, `web/index.html`, `lib/main.dart`
- Manifest: include `display_override: ["standalone", "minimal-ui"]`
